=/375x250/22c53bd1-14c1-4fed-9293-4ff77522ed52--Untitled_design.png, https://images.food52.com/2y2ZlobLHfuSRcG9EVlIm_0j1Ac=/750x500/22c53bd1-14c1-4fed-9293-4ff77522ed52--Untitled_design.png 2x\" src=\"https://images.food52.com/ISC0ziG1ibu8aVWxiG1klFbFxJ0=/2000x2000/22c53bd1-14c1-4fed-9293-4ff77522ed52--Untitled_design.png\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003ePhoto by Anna Arriaga\u003c/span\u003e\n            \u003c/p\u003e\n            \n\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eFormer Food Network star Giada De Laurentiis is trying to start a \u0026#34;chocolate pasta movement.” Recently, the Italian cook shared a childhood recipe on TikTok: \u003ca href=\"https://www.tiktok.com/@giadadelaurentiis/video/7446924116772293919?is_from_webapp=1\u0026amp;sender_device=pc\u0026amp;web_id=7378893596529788459\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ewarm pasta covered in hazelnut\u003c/a\u003e spread. Alarming? Buddy the Elf \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/blog/22237-a-definitive-ranking-of-the-best-movie-spaghetti-scenes\"\u003espaghetti\u003c/a\u003e level of craziness? Maybe, but I’m not going to knock it until I try it.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eChocolate pasta isn’t exactly new—it’s traditionally made in the Umbria and Tuscany regions of Italy, the big difference being that those traditional dishes use pasta noodles \u003cem\u003emade\u003c/em\u003e with chocolate rather than slathering pasta in chocolate spread. She also explains that it\u0026#39;s a special treat her mom used to make for her with chocolate sauce or even chocolate chips.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n\n\n              \u003cp\u003eIn her video, as she eats it she says “nothing is more comforting or feels like more of a hug.” If Giada says it\u0026#39;s good, there has to be some truth to it. I had to try making it myself.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n\n\n  \n\n              \u003cp\u003eTo start, all you need is small pasta shells and a jar of hazelnut spread. You can add chocolate chips for more nostalgic Giada flair if you’d like. Here’s how I made it, according to her instructions:\u003c/p\u003e\n              \u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBoil the pasta until cooked.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eServe warm noodles in a bowl.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTop warm noodles with a generous spoonful of hazelnut spread.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMix until fully combined. Eat and (try to) enjoy!\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n              \n\n  \u003cfigure\u003e\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\n      \u003ca href=\"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button\" data-pin-do=\"buttonPin\" data-pin-media=\"\" data-pin-description=\"The pasta in question.\" data-pin-custom=\"true\" data-ga-event=\"inPageInteraction\" data-ga-event-action=\"Pinterest Share\" data-ga-event-label=\"Article Body Image\" data-ga-destination-url=\"none\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 16.9 20.8\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M16.8 6.3C16.5 3.2 13.6.4 10.1.1 4.8-.5.1 2.7 0 7.9c0 2.4.8 4 2.9 4.8 1.5-1.5-.3-2.4-.5-4C2 4.3 7.1.1 11.7 2.9c3.2 1.9 2.6 9.9-1.2 10.7-.8.1-1.8-.1-2.1-.5-1.9-1.8 1.5-4.8.4-7.3-.9-2.1-3.6-.4-3.9 1.5-.2 1 .3 2 .3 2.9 0 2.1-1.3 5-1.7 7.1-.2.9-.3 2.6-.1 3.4h1.5c1-1.6 1.6-4.1 2.1-6.3.3-.2.5.4.7.6 1.8 1.4 5 .6 6.4-.7 2.1-1.7 3-5.2 2.7-8\" fill=\"currentColor\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n      \u003c/a\u003e\n\n      \u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==\" media=\"(min-width: 1400px)\" type=\"image/webp\" data-srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/uzzf9nH8ZLI6sJn2U3o0pKKS6is=/778x767/filters:format(webp)/86672734-43a2-4ffd-857e-ab2a9b1c4415--Screenshot_2024-12-19_at_12.25.07_PM.png, https://images.food52.com/7fpyNW5jhMlEiP9Iy_ivsCwC7_s=/1556x1534/filters:format(webp)/86672734-43a2-4ffd-857e-ab2a9b1c4415--Screenshot_2024-12-19_at_12.25.07_PM.png