-ab2a9b1c4415--Screenshot_2024-12-19_at_12.25.07_PM.png 2x\" alt=\"The pasta in question.\" width=\"964\" height=\"950\" data-expand=\"750\" data-srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/8GCvtLwebjUAGCLRMXQoTJOWnCU=/375x369/86672734-43a2-4ffd-857e-ab2a9b1c4415--Screenshot_2024-12-19_at_12.25.07_PM.png, https://images.food52.com/PeYgkTfBfM9r4Hi58cMk0e2lXc8=/750x738/86672734-43a2-4ffd-857e-ab2a9b1c4415--Screenshot_2024-12-19_at_12.25.07_PM.png 2x\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n      \u003cfigcaption\u003e\n          \u003cspan\u003eThe pasta in question.\u003c/span\u003e\n\n          \u003cspan\u003ePhoto by Anna Arriaga\u003c/span\u003e\n      \u003c/figcaption\u003e\n  \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n              \u003ch2\u003eThe Results\u003c/h2\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eFrom the get-go, the process of mixing hazelnut spread with warm, wet pasta was disgusting enough to put me off. But after incorporating the sauce well enough, it didn’t look too bad. Flavor wise, it just tasted like hazelnut spread with a weird, soggy pasta texture, and I kept thinking how much I would have enjoyed the two ingredients separately.  Maybe let\u0026#39;s stick to keeping pasta savory (we’ll make an exception for \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/recipes/78110-sheet-pan-mac-cheese-with-pumpkin-brown-butter\"\u003ethis pumpkin dish\u003c/a\u003e), and enjoying hazelnut spread on toast or fruit!\u003c/p\u003e\n              \u003chr/\u003e\n\n              \n              \u003ccenter\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eWhat trending recipe have you seen lately that we should try? Let us know in the comments.\u003c/em\u003e\n\u003c/center\u003e\n          \u003c/div\u003e\n      \u003c/div\u003e\n\n  \n  \u003cdiv\u003e\n      \u003ch3\u003ePopular on Food52\u003c/h3\u003e\n      \n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n  \n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
